headline: US stocks set another record and yields leap on signals the US economy is solid
summary: U.S. stocks climbed further into record heights on Thursday after a report showed the U.S. job market looks stronger than Wall Street expected.  The S&P 500 rose 0.8% and set an all-time high for the fourth time in five days.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average added 344 points, or 0.8%, and the Nasdaq composite gained 1%.

headline: What's Next for "BEACH" Stocks Amid Travel Season Uncertainty
summary: With the summer season upon us, travel stocks are back in focus. For that reason, eToro built an equal-weight basket of BEACH stocks — which include companies in bookings, entertainment, airlines, cruises, and hotels. Over the past year, these stocks have outperformed global indices, observes Bret Kenwell, US investment analyst at eToro.
